  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 364c2b772391e46dba637935c558b9b2, type: 3}
  m_Name: Myth_95
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::MythSO
  pageNumber: 95
  mythName: Myth 95
  omens:
  - '1. Black smoke on the horizon. The Lizard is

    birthed from the fire, blind
    and confused.

    It cannot bite yet and tries to flee.'
  - '2. A forest reduced to ash. A silver-haired

    bandit gathers it up. He knows
    that ash

    created by the Lizard is a deadly poison.'
  - '3. A river, flowing as grey ash-saturated

    sludge. Dead fish and newts line
    the

    riverbank. A pair of knightly

    salamanders, normally immune to all

    toxins,
    flail around in agonised rage.'
  - '4. A huge tail of the Lizard, detached by the

    growing beast, lies twitching
    amongst a

    briar patch. Its blood sparks a fire that

    can only be extinguished
    by seawater.'
  - '5. A burial mound, where the Lizard made a

    temporary nest, erupts into
    burning soil

    and ash (d8 Damage each turn within the

    area). It burns
    until midnight.'
  - '6. A heap of rocks, part melted, now the lair

    of the Lizard. If left to
    live it ignites into a

    huge fire that consumes the entire Hex,

    birthing
    four more Lizards to spread into

    neighbouring Realms.'
  verse: 
  castEntries:
  - name: The Lizard, the Land's Eternal Woe
    statBlock: 'VIG 18, CLA 12, SPI 5, 8 GD

      Scales of un-colour (ignores all
      Damage, but'
    notes: 'does not cover its belly)

      Bite (2d10, a wound incinerates the
      victim to

      ash) or thrash (d8 blast)

      Burning blood (a single drop
      sparks a fire.

      Only seawater can extinguish the flames)'
  - name: Yfran, Veteran Bandit
    statBlock: 'VIG 12, CLA 15, SPI 13, 6 GD

      A1 (black brigandine)'
    notes: '2 daggers (d6 each), bow (d6)

      Wants to pull off one last big job
      (see below).'
  - name: Knightly Salamander, Helmeck
    statBlock: 'VIG 10, CLA 4, SPI 5, 4 GD

      Claws and bite (d8), immune to
      most toxins'
    notes: 'O scale''d one afernal, portenter o''decay

      O fang o''roaring ruin,
      sunrise o''final day

      YFRAN''S BIG SCORE

      Target Plot

      1
      Retired Knight Murder

      2 Wandering Seer Identity theft

      3 The Seat
      of Power Burglary

      4 Neighbouring ruler Blackmail

      5 Wealthy commoner
      Confidence trick

      6 Rival bandit Long con

      Lizard

      Dwelling:
      Feasting hall ~ Sanctum: Timeless pool ~ Monument: Golden yew

      Hazard:
      Briar field ~ Curse: Acrid swamp ~ Ruin: Ghosts of slaughter

      The'
  flavorTable:
    title: 
    rows: []
  dwelling: Feasting hall
  sanctum: Timeless pool
  monument: Golden yew
  hazard: Briar field
  curse: Acrid swamp
  ruin: Ghosts of slaughter
  visibleByDefault: 0
  visibleMarkerPrefab: {fileID: 0}
